{
  "texts": [
    "Third, text-driven image generation models such as LDM focus primarily on single tasks such as text generation, overlooking the semantic understanding of images, potentially resulting in poor performance when handling complex relationships between text and images.",
    "In summary, existing LMMs face the following problems.1) Corpus limitations.",
    "Many multi-modal frameworks are trained on limited image-text pairs, potentially restricting their generalization abilities in real-world scenarios.",
    "2) Inconsistent understanding and generation capabilities across modalities.",
    "Inconsistencies in information fusion and understanding across different modalities may result in subpar performance in multi-modal scenarios."
  ]
}